# Stuff I've done

A loose collection of job description blurbs and my responses

Deﬁne and evolve the organizational data strategy and architecture, ensuring that data pipelines and models effectively serve the needs of the Product, Marketing, and Membership systems. 
→ Extensive experience building data products as an analytics leader and as a product manager building commercial analytics tools.

Design and oversee business data architecture—including data ﬂow designs, system integration, and schema management—to support robust lifecycle marketing and audience segmentation. 
→ I owned the data collection and processing for both Adobe Ad Cloud and Analytics. For Adobe I did extensive work with schema definition tools including mapping customer schemas to different standardized schemas. Data pipelines supported both measurement/analysis as well as segmentation and activation.

Establish data governance standards in collaboration with the Legal and Privacy teams. 
→ Worked closely with Adobe legal and privacy teams to ensure our data collection tools met legal requirements while providing maximum flexibility to customers. Consulted with customers to help them understand how to reach their analysis goals while respecting privacy. Acted a

Build and lead a team of analysts, architects, and visualization specialists to deliver high-quality dashboards, reports, and insights. 
→ At Adobe and Efficient Frontier I lead a team of analysts and data scientists who did custom analysis for customers while also building internal reporting tools to automate common analyses.

Translate complex data into clear narratives that inﬂuence strategy and operational priorities. 
→ I consider myself a strong communicator who has an excellent intuitive grasp data.

Conduct hands-on analysis (SQL, BI tools, Python/R, etc.) where needed to prototype solutions or guide the team. 
→ Experience with SQL and R along with standard BI tools like Power BI and Tableau

Excellent communication skills—able to translate data into actionable insights for technical and non-technical audiences. 
→ I am a strong communicator with experience in customer facing roles. At Efficient Frontier and Ad Cloud I was part of a team (and later manager of that team) that worked as data scientist consultants supporting customers. This included pre-sales conversations, weekly operations and quarterly reviews with executives. 
→ As a product manager I have extensive experience talking to customers to gather information as well as to communicate roadmap and vision. 
Strong understanding of data governance, compliance, and privacy issues.
→ As PM for Data Collection for Adobe Analytics and Customer Journey Analytics data privacy and governance were a primary concern for our products. I developed extensive expertise in privacy regulations like GDPR, ePrivacy Directive, CCPA and others.
